16/06/2008
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Prime Minister Nikola Spiric will sign the long-awaited Stabilisation and Association Agreement (SAA) with the EU at a ceremony in Luxembourg on Monday (June 16th). Though actual EU membership could be a decade away, an interim accord to enforce new customs' tariffs and quotas will be effective on July 1st.
At the weekend, Republika Sprska Prime Minister Milorad Dodik said the SAA would open new opportunities and would attract more foreign investors. BiH Presidency Chairman Haris Silajdzic said the accord will bring a number of trade benefits and would increase BiH's access to EU financing. (Dnevni Avaz, Nezavisne Novine, BBC - 16/06/08; Fena, RTRS - 15/06/08)
